We start by identifying the “Initial” equity contributions. In our table the first three rows are of type “Initial20231231001”. Their amounts are listed as follows:
• Cash deposit: 3,000,000.0  
• Bank deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Fixed Assets: 8,000,000.0  

The initial paid‐in capital is the sum of these amounts:
  3,000,000.0 + 5,000,000.0 + 8,000,000.0 = 16,000,000.0

Because no additional equity injections are present among the later transactions (which affect purchases, expenses, sales, etc.), the ending (final) paid‐in capital remains the same as the initial amount.
